          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #22\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    The slow PP-DocLayout smoke test downloads a large model on cold cache, but default tests do not exclude slow tests.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Default CI can depend on Hugging Face availability and cache state.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `tests/layout/test_pp_doclayout.py:26`\n- `tests/layout/test_pp_doclayout.py:37`\n- `pyproject.toml:340`\n- `Makefile:70`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Exclude slow tests by default with -m 'not slow'.\n- [ ] Add a scheduled/manual integration job for model-download smoke tests.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:04:25Z",
